## 4. UI/UX Best Practices Guide

### Visual Hierarchy & Clarity
-   **Typography**: Stick to the "Major Third" or "Perfect Fourth" scale. Don't mix more than 2 fonts (which the project currently adheres to).
-   **Contrast**: Always ensure text meets WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 ratio). The current "Sage & Stone" theme is good but needs verifying on the `#2D5A41` usage.

### Interaction Design
-   **Feedback**: Every interactive element (button, link, input) implies a state change. Ensure `:hover`, `:active`, and `:focus-visible` states are clearly defined (The [Button](file:///home/rocky/Projects/Pet-Adoption-Platform-Django-React/frontend/src/components/common/Buttons/Button.jsx#5-49) component does this well).
-   **Consistency**: A "Submit" button on the Login page should look identical to a "Save" button on the Settings page.

### Code Hygiene for Recruiters
-   **Clean Imports**: Group imports (React, 3rd party, Local).
-   **Prop Types**: Ensure all reusable components (like [Button](file:///home/rocky/Projects/Pet-Adoption-Platform-Django-React/frontend/src/components/common/Buttons/Button.jsx#5-49)) have `PropTypes` defined (Currently doing well here).
-   **No Inline Styles**: Move `style={{ filter: ... }}` to a CSS class if used more than once.

